message: lerna bootstrap
Fixing published version of react-server

Attempt at travis integration

Also pulled eslint config up to the top-level and added some README badges.

Pick up a minor lerna bugfix

https://github.com/kittens/lerna/issues/58

Attempt to unhork the build by pulling integration tests out into their own directory outside of packages and the purview of lerna. Also moved a test helper file from integration tests back into react-server where it belongs, which makes react-server's test suite run correctly again. I've tested these changes locally, but builds are tricky things. Pushing to the PR to see if it works on Travis.

Upgrade lerna to latest beta

Because it actually works.
Better travis through npm

Get rid of base gulpfile and gulp-chug

Just run tests with `npm test`

Briefly tried to get integration tests back into `packages/`, but gave up
after an hour or so.  Layers of impediment there.

Move devDependencies up to top level

This speeds up bootstrap and reduces storage requirements.

These packages are developed in the context of the monorepo.  No need for them
to independently install their dev dependencies.  This also helps us stay on
common versions across packages.

This required updating the top-level eslint config, and fixing some eslint
errors that the old version let slip through the cracks in the main
`react-server` package and `react-server-cli`.

Note that I left `react-server` on babel 5.  That's a whole other can of worms.

Move integration tests into packages/

This reduces top-level `npm test` (travis) time and eliminates an odd-man-out.
Trimmed a little too much off of the top-level test target

Re-distribute module tagger dev dependency

It's location-dependent.  Don't want the `react-server.packages.` prefix.

Move tagger back to top and trim prefixes

Eliminates a bootstrap race with relative deps.

Re-add "stage-1" features

Still using these down-stream.  Always had them.  No need to remove.

- Cleans up the top-level package.json

Hoisting was introduce in
